China> Iran and China are linked by common economic and commercial interests. In fact, Iranian oil is needed to advance Chinese economic development. A vital business for Tehran that makes Beijing's influence on ayatollah strong. China expressed concern and demanded moderation, but had received the call from Blinken, who asked Foreign Minister Wang Yi to intervene to appease Tehran. However it is to be seen whether China will follow Washington's recommendations or whether, as in the past, it will think to play its game behind the scenes to annoy the White House.&nbsp;
